President Obama congratulates General Lloyd J. Austin on his retirement after 41 years of service to the country. General Austin's character and competence exemplify what America demands of its military leaders. As Commander, U.S. Central Command, General Austin oversaw military operations in Iraq, Afghanistan, and the broader counter-ISIL campaign. The President relied on his wise judgment and steadfast leadership in navigating the challenges in the region. General Austin's role as Commander of U.S. forces in Iraq was instrumental in allowing Iraqis to take the lead in securing their own future. The President is confident that General Austin will continue to find ways to serve his country in retirement.